(85,'D807','HALL, DOUGLAS V.','MICROPROCESSORS & INTERFACING','005.26HAL','ELECTRONICS','5//9','Covers the fundamentals of microprocessor operation, bus interfacing, and peripheral device connectivity. Includes memory mapping, interrupt handling, DMA, and serial/parallel communication techniques. A practical reference for electronics and computer engineering students.','#7C3AED','microprocessors'),
